==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Middle English]] ''[[-orie]]'' (from [[Latin]] adjective suffix ''[[-ōrius]]'')<ref name="heritage">{{R:American Heritage 2000|-ory}}</ref>.

===Adjective Suffix===
'''-ory'''

# of or pertaining to; adjective suffix appended to various words, often nouns, to make an adjective form. Often added to words of Latin origin, but used with other words also<ref name="heritage" />
#: ''[[excrete]] and [[excretory]], [[sense]] and [[sensory]], [[statute]] and [[statutory]].''

